In [Connecting JIRA to SQL Server 2008|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA/Connecting+JIRA+to+SQL+Server+2008] documentation, it is said that the database collation type has to be *case-insensitive* {{SQL_Latin1_General_CP437_CI_AI}}. But in other products, such as [Stash|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/STASH/Connecting+Stash+to+SQL+Server] and [Confluence|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Database+Setup+for+SQL+Server], it has to be *case-sensitive* {{SQL_Latin1_General_CP1_CS_AS}}.

This setting could lead to problem during installation, upgrade and/or startup. Related JAC ticket: JRA-21506, JRA-37538.

Is there any particular reason we have case insensitive for JIRA and all the other products are case sensitive? We want to double check that it's correct - thanks. :)

