I do a lot of scoping of cases for developers and what oftentimes happens is that by the time a case gets to me, there are dozens of comments, most of them irrelevant. So what I want to do is emphasize the important comments or even the summary and the way I usually do it is something like "h1. Ignore all comments before my comment on _some date_" which is pretty hacky.

What would be great is to be able to star, check, or promote (or whatever verb you want) comments on a thread. Maybe in the set of icons on the right (where the link and edit icons are). Then when other people open the case, only the starred comments are expanded and the rest are collapsed. That way we can present a concise thread to a developer of how we arrived at the case.

What do you guys think?

