When you rename a user on the LDAP side for a delegated directory in JIRA, the user needs to log in first in order for the rename to take effect. 

This can be useful for small directories, but for larger, enterprise-size userbases, this is unacceptable when company-wide user policy changes are made. For example, changing the username attribute to another attribute, which will cause a mass rename on the entire user directory. 

If we have a "switch" that we can flip to force a "sync", this problem will be resolved. Its understandable that Delegated directories are not meant to be synced, but its good to have the option for usecases like the above.

