According to the documentation for the "Create a new issue or add a comment to an existing issue" [(found here)|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/JIRA061/Creating+Issues+and+Comments+from+Email#CreatingIssuesandCommentsfromEmail-Createanewissueoraddacommenttoanexistingissue], "...if an email message contains an issue key in its subject line and that issue key exists in your JIRA installation, the handler will add the email message content as a comment on the issue, regardless of which project the issue is in."

JIRA Admins who configure these email handlers would like email with issue keys in projects other than the specified project to be ignored by the handler.  For example, if the email handler is configured for issues in Project X, but receives an email with an issue for Project Y in the subject, it should ignore that email rather than add a comment to that existing issue.  A separate email handler should be set up for that other project.

h3. Steps to Reproduce: 

# Configure a user directory with NESTED groups option enabled;
# Create a nested group;
# Configure the notification scheme to send e-mail notification to a parent user-group;

h3. Expected Results:

JIRA should send the notification to all group members including child members of the nested group;

H3. Actual Results: 

JIRA only sends to notification to the direct members of the parent group.

